                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "I don\u2019t think we want to add this now. Marco is working on the configure-service requirements for OpenBMC. \n\nIf we were going to do this, we should do it for all systems and not just Minerva."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Marco Kawajiri",
                        "email": "kawajiri@meta.com",
                        "username": "kawmarco"
                    },
                    "message": "Hi Yang, do you have more context on this change? Was this a request from Meta?\n\nI've been discussing with Jagpal on the /mnt/data problem, will add him to the review as well"
                },
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Jagpal S Gill",
                        "email": "paligill@gmail.com",
                        "username": "jagpalgill"
                    },
                    "message": "Marco, Thanks for adding me to the review.\n\nYang,\nWe tested that on Qemu we could do \"mkdir -p /var/meta && ln -sf /var/meta/ /mnt/data\" and it works fine. We are trying to harmonize the dir structure for FB openBMC and LF openBMC configure service. So, one of the init scripts can perform this operation. Also, i agree with Patrick that this change to mount persistent storage is needed for all Meta platforms and not just Minerva, hence the change should go into some Meta's global yocto layer so it can be applied across all platforms."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Yang Chen",
                        "email": "yang.chen@quantatw.com",
                        "username": "Quanta-YangChen"
                    },
                    "message": "Patrick, Marco and Jagpal,\n\nCould I put this file to the /meta-facebook/recipes-phosphor/initrdscripts/phosphor-static-norootfs-init/ and change the name to 95-mount-persistent-fb for all platforms of Meta use?"
                }
