                    "message": "@Jagpal - Can you work with Quanta team on the desired solution here?"
                },
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Yang Chen",
                        "email": "yang.chen@quantatw.com",
                        "username": "Quanta-YangChen"
                    },
                    "message": "Hi Jagpal,\n\nDo you have any recommendations for the solution? Thanks."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Jagpal S Gill",
                        "email": "paligill@gmail.com",
                        "username": "jagpalgill"
                    },
                    "message": "@Yang,\n\nHere is the POR after our internal discussions on this topic -\n\n1. PE will have /mnt/data available for both LF and Meta BMC platforms. This will be backed by a persistent store. Hence, there won't be any changes needed on PE side to support configure BMC (for LF platforms).\n2. Bletchley:\n2.a. Patrick posted a PR to create /mnt/emmc.\nhttps://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/openbmc/+/68248 (Already Merged).\n2.b. This will be used by PWM team to host Mac Mini images. Right now, both /mnt/data and /mnt/emmc will point to same persistent storage. Bletchley PE team has created a task to start using /mnt/emmc to host Mac Mini images. \n3. As next step, /mnt/data will be mounted/symlinked to use persistent NOR flash as thats the one being used on all other platforms. This change will go into common LF openBMC meta layer (Bletchley will be modified to use common change). Following PR will be updated to reflect this POR -\nhttps://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/openbmc/+/67837\n\n----\n\nAs stated above, you would need to implement Step 3 as part of this PR. You can make the change and get them reviewed and we can merge them once Bletchley PE team is done implementing task in the 2.b step."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "PL",
                        "email": "potin.lai@quantatw.com",
                        "username": "potinlai"
                    },
                    "message": "Hi @Jagpal,\n\nDoes this means all Meta's platform (including Bletchley) will mount /mnt/data on persistent NOR flash?\n\nSo Bletchley will mount storages as below in the future, am I correct?\n\n- /mnt/data --> NOR flash\n- /mnt/emmc --> emmc"
                },
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Jagpal S Gill",
                        "email": "paligill@gmail.com",
                        "username": "jagpalgill"
                    },
                    "message": "Hi @Yang\n\nAs per my understanding, for all other platforms (non LF based platforms), /mnt/data is already backed by persistent NOR flash. By making this change we are brining the LF platforms in sync.\n\nYes, Bletchley will mount storage as you indicated. Once Bletchley team PE team makes the change to use /mnt/emmc for mac mini image provisioning this change can be merged.\n\nIn meantime, you can make the change as i mentioned in Step 3 and have it ready and reviewed. Please make sure to keep the change in common layer and make any changes on Bletchley layers to accomodate it. Thanks"
                },
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Yang Chen",
                        "email": "yang.chen@quantatw.com",
                        "username": "Quanta-YangChen"
                    },
                    "message": "Hi @Japal,\n\nSo should we just install the /mnt/data for all Meta's platforms without checking the MACHINE_FEATURES first to filter the fb-secondary-emmc? If yes, we can submit another patchset to do this. Thanks"
                },
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "Hi Yang.  Please just hold off on this commit and I'll get it fixed up once we are in a good place on Bletchley.  There is no rush for this."
                },
                {
                    "file": "meta-facebook/recipes-phosphor/initrdscripts/phosphor-static-norootfs-init/95-mount-persistent-fb",
